data.name: Classic Minestrone Soup
data.quickTastyDescription: A hearty and comforting soup filled with vegetables, beans, and pasta, perfect for any meal.
detailedCookingInstructions: In a large pot, heat olive oil over medium heat.
Add the chopped onion, carrot, and celery; saut√© for about 5 minutes until softened.
Stir in the garlic, zucchini, and green beans; cook for another 3 minutes.
Add the diced tomatoes, vegetable broth, and cannellini beans; bring to a boil.
Stir in the pasta and reduce to a simmer. Cook for about 10 minutes or until the pasta is tender.
Add the fresh spinach and cook for an additional 2 minutes until wilted.
Season with salt, pepper, and Italian seasoning to taste.
Serve hot, topped with grated Parmesan cheese.
data.modifiersForBase: Classic version with a variety of vegetables and pasta
